## Approach

<!-- Keep one of the two sections below, delete the other -->

### Drafting Approach
1. Read source materials from `source/`
2. Read relevant shared reference from `~/repos/dotbrain/reference/`
3. Draft into `drafts/<deliverable>.md`
4. Convert to final format in `output/`

### Review Approach
1. Read source document from `source/`
2. Read relevant shared reference from `~/repos/dotbrain/reference/`
3. Produce review/analysis into `drafts/`
4. Generate final output to `output/`

## Voice & Style

- <e.g., Formal, third person, present tense>
- <e.g., Australian English spelling>
- <e.g., Numbers: spell out one–nine, numerals for 10+>

## Shared Reference

Read from `~/repos/dotbrain/reference/` on demand:
- `company/company.md` — group structure, key people
- `company/terminology.md` — business terms, style rules
- `company/standards.md` — document formatting, compliance

## Directory Structure

```
source/          # Read-only reference materials
drafts/          # Working documents (one file per deliverable)
output/          # Generated artifacts (gitignored)
tasks/
  todo.md        # Deliverable checklist
  lessons.md     # Corrections from prior sessions
```

## Tasks

- Track deliverables in `tasks/todo.md`
- Record corrections in `tasks/lessons.md`
- When updating a shared figure, grep `drafts/` for the same figure and update all instances
